My one present to Kalsto was giving him a white robe, not that ugly trak's teeth one, but that awesome befallen one. I forget the name of it... <br>
<br>
he actually wore it for a while until he had the manna robe. <br>
<br>
Kalsto's guild, took me from a ignorant to the high-end game, small guildminded 50 Bard (Lenaleni told me to lie, and say I was 51, so he'd tag me) to a lvl 56 Bard who actually was learning a bit about raiding. I was always impressed with Kalsto's ability, alot of what I have to say, matches what Biffin's recently posted at Vis msg board. <br>
<br>
Like Gaelron tho, I sometimes found it hard to endure his lack of patience. It boiled down to him being extremely talented, yet having to wait, and do things over and over, because of some random new-to-raiding player. And well, although he was talented, and a very skilled/smart player, I will always hate Choppa, and unfortunately, he was at times, Kalsto's righthand man. <br>
<br>
At one point, Vis was leaps ahead of everybody else, and Wraith/Descent/Lotus were all pretty much the same. Then well it all changed :P<br>
<br>
Btw, Does Shim and Kal #2 play in that guild?<br>
<br>
As for Spiritjazz, yah, who could forget the mithril bp, and crazy colors that female wood-elf had on. Spiritjazz spoke to my bard on a number of occaisons from her many twinks. <br>
